@BlueBooksandBs Bye! *waves* Good luck reading!

RT @creativedeeds: A8: You were gonna read anyway right? Why not have fun with  other awesome readers? A no pressure week of reading crazin…
@BlueBooksandBs Aww, thank you! :)
A8: Because you learn that being a reader means you are part of a community of super-friendly, awesome people. Y'all are great! #boutofbooks
@Odrah Yep, I do this too. :) Sometimes it's okay to judge a book by its cover.
A7: Definitely Goodreads and fellow bloggers. Those two sources have made me set for life with book recs. #boutofbooks
@respire_think Oh my gosh it is SO good. You will love it. :)
A6: Under a Painted Sky by Stacey Lee. Feminism, diversity, romance, and the era of pioneers and gold-diggers. #boutofbooks
A6: Jane Eyre by Charlotte Bronte because Gothic lit and a dreamy guy. Classic for a reason. #boutofbooks
A6: You should most definitely read Enchantress From the Stars by Sylvia Engdahl. Older book but so deep and creative! #boutofbooks
@BookBender @soulswallo Yay! :D
A5: Bad days require books and chocolate. Or ice cream. Or chocolate ice cream. #boutofbooks
A5: Bad days require books that make me feel ALL THE FEELS!!! And laughter is good too. #boutofbooks
RT @Jinkiesbooks: Bad days require books with sarcasm. Lots of sarcasm #boutofbooks
@BlueBooksandBs Waterbending: elegant, graceful--and deadly.
RT @soulswallo: The worst thing about a #boutofbooks chat is how I can't stop adding the hashtag to everything for HOURS after.
A4: Oh and I would be an old wise woman who gives advice but is really just messing with everyone. #boutofbooks
@Odrah YES ME TOO!!!
A4: I would be Katara from Avatar: The Last Airbender. 'Nuff said. #boutofbooks
RT @bookjunkie54: A3. I'm a reader who can't stop buying books even though I have more than I'll ever read. #bookaddict #boutofbooks
@YouBookMe It's okay, I'm the same way. :) They were enjoyable but not fantastic in my opinion.
@bookpubreads The struggle is real. :P
A3: I'm also known for having book cravings. Sometimes I just NEED that ONE book and I don't have it and it's awful. #boutofbooks
@LittleBookStar lol XD Yeah, I'm trying to cut back and be a more realistic list-maker...
@OutlandishLit Thanks! XD
A3: Hmm... I'm a reader who is known for making long lists of books I intend to read but never will. My record was over 18,000. #boutofbooks
RT @itsme_lori: Tons of tweets about to come for the #boutofbooks chat. Sorry to anyone not participating. Just ignore me!
@Odrah Right?! Somebody understands. :)
